# China Mainland Server Network

The project deploy host (`119.45.36.208`, `/opt/loanagent`) is in **mainland China**. Direct pulls from Docker Hub, GHCR, PyPI, npm, etc. are often slow or blocked. Always prefer mainland mirrors for remote install/build/deploy.

## Docker

- Prefer DaoCloud-prefixed images already used on this host, e.g.:
  - `docker.m.daocloud.io/library/postgres:16-alpine`
  - `docker.m.daocloud.io/library/python:3.12.11-slim-bookworm`
  - `docker.m.daocloud.io/emqx/emqx:5.8.6`
  - `docker.m.daocloud.io/library/node:22.14.0-bookworm-slim`
- Host `/etc/docker/daemon.json` may already set `"registry-mirrors": ["https://docker.m.daocloud.io"]` — still use explicit DaoCloud image names when Hub pulls stall.
- Server Dockerfiles: `docker/control-plane/Dockerfile.server` (mirrored bases). Prefer it over Hub/GHCR bases for remote builds.
- Reuse images already present on the host (`docker images`) instead of re-pulling when possible.

## Python / uv / apt

- Prefer Tsinghua / Aliyun / Douban PyPI mirrors when installing on the server (pip/`uv` index URL).
- Prefer Aliyun / Tsinghua apt mirrors for Debian/Ubuntu package installs on the server.

## Do not

```bash
# ❌ BAD — often hangs from this host
docker pull postgres:16.9-alpine
docker pull ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:...

# ✅ GOOD
docker pull docker.m.daocloud.io/library/postgres:16-alpine
# build with Dockerfile.server / compose.server.yaml mirrored images
```

Local Mac Docker Compose (`infra/compose.yaml`) may keep digest-pinned Hub images for reproducibility; **server** deploy (`infra/compose.server.yaml`) must stay mirror-friendly.
